7. The Princess’s Lock (Factorial) 
Story: 
The princess is locked behind n magical locks. 
She can only unlock them in every possible order. 
�
�
 How many ways can she open them? (factorial) 
Input: 
● Integer n. 
Output: 
● Factorial of n. 
Constraints: 
● 1 <= n <= 12

CODE :
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int factorial(int n) {
    if (n == 1) return 1;
    return n * factorial(n - 1);
}

int main() {
    int n;
    cin >> n;
    cout << factorial(n);
    return 0;
}
